 | A-038 | 005C2 does not write audit rows for application object-access denials, and treats `credit_manager` role access as a source-backed global override only once an application is in the `credit_assessment` stage. Created/received users remain the implemented Field Officer-style owner facts until assignment queues are modeled. | Existing application audit conventions record successful create/update/submit/reference actions, while no existing authorization-denial audit convention exists for application endpoints. `auth-permissions.md` §19.2 gives Credit Manager access to the Credit Assessment domain, and the current schema represents that domain with `LoanApplication.current_stage = credit_assessment` but has no richer queue or assignment table yet. | `docs/source/auth-permissions.md` §19.2, §34.3, §37.3; `docs/slices/005C2-application-object-access-hardening.md`; `docs/working/digests/epic-005-application-intake.md` | 005C2-application-object-access-hardening and future application assignment/completeness slices | Medium | Yes | 2026-07-09 | Future assignment/queue slices should replace the created/received-only scope with explicit assigned-user/team facts, and add denial audit rows if a project-wide authorization-denial audit convention is introduced. |
 | A-039 | 005D implements `POST /api/v1/loan-applications/{loan_application_id}/document-checklist/refresh/` as a derived read operation gated by `applications.loan_application.read`; it does not persist checklist rows, write audit/workflow events, or invent a new checklist-refresh permission. | Source documents name a checklist refresh endpoint but the source-backed permission catalogue provides application read/upload/verify and broad document-checklist permissions without an exact application-checklist refresh mutation rule. A read-derived refresh keeps the endpoint available for clients without creating unsourced business authority or side effects. | `docs/working/digests/epic-005-application-intake.md`; `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §20-§21 as distilled; `docs/source/auth-permissions.md` §12.4 as distilled | 005D-application-document-checklist and future completeness/checklist slices | Medium | Yes | 2026-07-09 | 005E or a later completeness owner should replace this with persisted checklist/evaluation state only when the exact refresh side effects and permission are source-confirmed. |
 | A-040 | 005F `return-with-deficiencies` accepts `items[].item_code` selected from current 005E blocking checklist facts, rather than the source §19.7 example's `deficiency_ids`. | The source API example assumes deficiency rows already exist before return, but 005E deliberately did not persist deficiency rows and 005F's scope is to create them from blocking completeness facts. Accepting source-backed item codes prevents arbitrary free-form deficiencies while allowing the return action to create the first deficiency records. | `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §19.7 and §21.1-§21.2; `docs/source/data-model.md` §13.5; `docs/slices/005F-deficiency-creation-and-resolution.md`; `docs/working/digests/epic-005-application-intake.md` | 005F-deficiency-creation-and-resolution and future portal deficiency response slices | Medium | Yes | 2026-07-09 | If a future source update requires a separate "draft deficiencies" creation step before return, add that endpoint and adapt `return-with-deficiencies` to accept persisted `deficiency_ids` while keeping item-code validation at creation time. |
+| A-041 | 005F2 blocks additional `return-with-deficiencies` attempts once an application is already `application_status = incomplete_returned`. | The opened source docs define the first deficiency return to incomplete state and borrower resubmission, but do not define repeat staff returns before resubmission. Blocking repeats avoids duplicate open deficiency rows and duplicate borrower communications without inventing a repeat-return business rule. | `docs/source/data-model.md` `loan_application_status`; `docs/source/functional-spec.md` M03 deficiency flow; `docs/source/screen-spec.md` S12; `docs/slices/005F2-deficiency-return-status-contract-hardening.md` | 005F2-deficiency-return-status-contract-hardening and future portal deficiency response/resubmission slices | Medium | Yes | 2026-07-09 | Future borrower resubmission work should define the source-backed transition from `incomplete_returned` back to submitted/completeness review before any later repeat-return behavior is allowed. |
